claim.claim-text:
A brake disc, rotating about its own axis of rotation (1a), comprising a brake strip (2), an element (3) for supporting the brake strip (2) and a plurality of first elements (4) for connecting the brake strip (2) with the supporting element (3) which can be elastically deformed in such a way as to allow a relative movement of the brake strip (2) with respect to the supporting element (3);

characterized in that

the supporting element (3) comprises at least a first component (7) and a second component (8) connected to the brake strip (2) by means of the first connecting (4); a plurality of second connecting elements (9) of the first component (7) and of the second component (8) are elastically deformable in such a way as to allow a relative movement between the first component (7) and the second component (8).
